apping that to its \\\"doMain\\\" method, which takes a string array as a parameter. I'm wondering if this approach covers dynamic access and potentially includes a reflection call for the active class. It's important to ensure I'm considering all necessary factors for the configuration to work smoothly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qyx10MAfx12ivgMG3WOuVbCT|fc_0f807a1903e676200169f57e5309188197a5615a88adb7d937", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/src/test/java/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/WebAppCreatorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_gwtproject.gwt_user;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.google.gwt.user.tools.WebAppCreator;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n\npublic class WebAppCreatorTest {\n    private static final String MODULE_NAME = \"org_gwtproject.gwt_user.coverage.CoverageApp\";\n\n    @TempDir\n    private Path outputDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void mainFlowGeneratesReadmeTemplateFromClasspathResources() throws Throwable {\n        final boolean generated = invokeDoMain(\n                \"-templates\", \"readme\",\n                \"-out\", outputDirectory.toString(),\n                MODULE_NAME);\n\n        assertThat(generated).isTrue();\n        assertThat(outputDirectory.resolve(\"README.txt\"))\n                .exists()\n                .content()\n                .contains(\"Generated by GWT WebAppCreator\")\n                .contains(\"CoverageApp\");\n    }\n\n    private static boolean invokeDoMain(final String... args) throws Throwable {\n        final MethodHandle doMain = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(\n                        WebAppCreator.class,\n                        MethodHandles.lookup())\n                .findStatic(\n                        WebAppCreator.class,\n                        \"doMain\",\n                        MethodType.methodType(boolean.class, String[].class));\n        return (boolean) doMain.invoke((Object) args);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4664, "output": 1552, "cacheRead": 104960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 111176, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777696319653, "responseId": "resp_0f807a1903e676200169f57e406e30819786d21d5df8b4f194"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_qyx10MAfx12ivgMG3WOuVbCT|fc_0f807a1903e676200169f57e5309188197a5615a88adb7d937", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1755 bytes to tests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/src/test/java/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/WebAppCreatorTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777696340695}]}
